[04:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'seduce guys and smoothly steal their wallets in an alley. Stylish, rhythmic, really dope. So, the first and most important tip, the visuals in a music video should not literally match the'

[04:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'lyrics. That\'s considered bad taste. Use imagery and associative sequences to make the viewer think about what the song is saying and what the artist wants to convey. Showing exactly what\'s being sung is boring and primitive. A good'

[04:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'music video should complement the song, not retell it. It can convey the same mood, but in an unexpected way, giving the viewer something to think about or simply making it cool to watch. However, if in a rap video about money, we show a'

[05:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'lavish lifestyle, that\'s not bad taste because it\'s not an illustration of the lyrics, but a demonstration of real success. Those things are part of the truth, not just a made-up video concept.'

[05:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Second tip for making a video with neural networks, references. First, create the images, color palettes, and other elements you want to show. I used Pinterest. I searched for'

[05:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'pictures, then edited them using Nano Banana for later use, upscaling, changing aspect ratios. It\'s very important to include references in the prompt for SeaDance 2.0 so that the AI understands which character or object is'

[05:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'where and what they are doing. Third tip about lip sync in SeaDance 2.0. In addition to images, we can also attach audio files of our song to the generation. However, SeaDance 2.0'

[05:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'doesn\'t always recognize the words correctly, so it\'s also important to specify in the prompt the lyrics that are being sung in the audio clip. This is especially noticeable when the song has an accent or very fast rapping.'

[06:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Now, let\'s move on to the rap video about the rapper and his riches. As I said, I started by looking for references. After that, [music] I polished them a bit with Nano Banana'

[06:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Pro. I made a collage of the main character, a shot of a Rolls-Royce, a room with plants, an evening pool on a yacht, a diamond airplane, a view from behind the wheel of a Maybach, a penthouse in a'

[06:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'skyscraper, and a safe room. Then I cut the track into pieces and generated lip sync scenes for each part. In the prompt, I added the words the main character should say. There\'s a small'

[06:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'nuance. When the rapper is in the background, his outline start to blur, so I often use this addition to the prompt, multi-faceted close-up shooting, action scenes, to clearly show the rapper in the frame.'

[06:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'I made transitions between scenes using the first and last frame. The main thing is to describe exactly how the transition should look. For example, the main character is lying in a pool on a'

[07:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'yacht, the camera flies up through the clouds where the diamond plane is located. If we don\'t describe that, the transition will most likely look messy. After all the generations, it\'s time for'

[07:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'editing, adding transitions, effects, and a bit of color correction. Render, and voila, the video is ready. I used exactly the same method for the rock music video. I used an associative'

[07:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'sequence about a racer who finds strength, doesn\'t give up, and pushes through to victory. As references, I processed only four images: the main character, his car, his antagonist, and'

[07:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the antagonist\'s car. I made full-body collages of the characters, their heads, and collages of the cars from different angles. I described all the surroundings in the prompt in SeaArt 2.0. Since this'

[08:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'is an anime style, I also mentioned that in the prompt so the AI wouldn\'t drift toward realism. If you\'re making a video and don\'t know what to show on screen, ask a text-based neural network for help, like ChatGPT or similar. You give'

[08:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'it the song\'s lyrics and say, "Come up with music video ideas that are interesting, not just literally showing the lyrics." Or more specifically, "I\'m stuck. The hero is singing about a broken heart. What should I show on'

[08:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'screen?" The AI will suggest metaphors, storylines, imagery, and cuts. [music] I use this method myself, and I think it\'s fine. It saves time.'

[08:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'By the way, videos that tell a story are easier to make. There\'s no lip sync, and you don\'t need transitions based on the first and last frame because the best transition here is a match cut. After all the generations, I simply edited the'

[08:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'footage without any extra effects and applied a bit of color correction. &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; Now, the Japanese Phonk video. Here, we used both visual'

[09:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'storytelling and lip sync. As usual, I made collages of the main characters and generated individual elements to be used in the video. It\'s important to note,'

[09:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'SeaArt 2.0, like any other neural network, does not produce the same result twice with the same prompt. A small tip to save money on generation, if a particular shot turns out bad,'

[09:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'regenerate only that shot, not the whole video. In editing, you simply replace the bad shot with a better one. Sometimes extra characters appear in frames or they are positioned incorrectly. So, don\'t forget to include'

[09:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'references in the prompt using input one, input two. That way the AI will know exactly which character is where and what they should be doing. If generating weapons gives you trouble, just add the word toy before the weapon.'

[09:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'That should work. After generating all the videos, edit, apply a little color correction, and voila, another video is ready. 30% off every generation on SeaDance. Link in'

[10:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the description. Well, can you already feel production companies slowly turning their heads toward developing neural networks? A similar music video that used to cost $10,000 can now be made in a couple of'

[10:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'evenings without leaving your chair for about 100 bucks. Think about that now. So, you\'ll stay ahead of the game. Bye.'
